    - target: {fileID: 3644449064964374390, guid: 80b79820afb89ab4881f29906205b0e1, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_text
      value: The Earth spins on its axis. This spinning is called rotation. Because
        the Earth rotates, different parts face the Sun and then move away from it.
        This causes day and night. As the Earth rotates, the Sun seems to move across
        the sky, and shadows change in length and direction during the day.
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 3644449064964374390, guid: 80b79820afb89ab4881f29906205b0e1, type: 3}
      propertyPath: m_fontSize
